    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The tracking data reveals a sustained and deliberate global military posture characterized by high-value asset deployments across key theaters. Strategic airlift operations (C-17, KC-135) and maritime patrol aircraft (P-8) dominate the air domain, indicating robust logistics and surveillance capabilities, particularly in the Pacific and Southern Hemisphere. Carrier Strike Group deployments—USS Gerald R. Ford in the Caribbean and USS George Washington in the Philippine Sea—demonstrate a deliberate effort to maintain forward presence in response to regional tensions and deterrence requirements. The inclusion of training and ISR operations in Europe, including slow-moving, high-altitude aircraft likely conducting electronic warfare or signals intelligence, underscores a multi-domain approach to regional security. Naval deployments in the Mediterranean and Pacific reflect a balanced strategy of power projection and crisis response. The data also highlights allied interoperability efforts, such as U.S. support for French submarine operations and South Korea&#39;s long-range submarine deployment to Canada, signaling expanding Indo-Pacific partnerships. Overall, the posture reflects a global military strategy emphasizing rapid deployment, allied collaboration, and deterrence, with a focus on the Pacific and Middle East while maintaining flexibility in secondary theaters. Recent reports on Iran’s nuclear program and NATO’s 2025 annual report further contextualize the strategic environment driving these deployments.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
